== Spell Secrets ==

=== Sacrifice ===
The Moonbrooke princess can learn Sacrifice:
* Kills the caster
* Attempts to destroy all enemies
* Only works on some enemy types

=== Return ===
Returns party to last visited save point:
* Essential for dungeon exploration
* Saves on travel time

== Easter Eggs ==

=== Starting Town Names ===
Towns are named after the three heroes:
* Cannock - Prince of Cannock
* Moonbrooke - Princess of Moonbrooke
* Lorasia - Hero's kingdom

=== Dragon Quest References ===
Many locations reference Dragon Warrior 1:
* Tantegel returns
* Charlock Castle can be revisited
* Erdrick's legacy continues

== Tips ==

'''Early Game:'''
* Focus on reaching Moonbrooke princess first
* Magic users make early game easier
* Grind before entering first major dungeon

'''Mid Game:'''
* Boat access opens exploration
* Collect crests systematically
* Stock up on healing items

'''End Game:'''
* Rhone enemies are very difficult
* Level 25+ recommended for final boss
* Multiple attempts at Hargon common

== Known Issues ==

=== Difficulty Spike ===
Dragon Warrior II is known for:
* Sudden difficulty increase in Rhone
* Expensive resurrection costs
* Limited save points in late game

=== Grinding Requirements ===
Compared to other games in the series:
* More grinding required
* Metal Slimes helpful but rare
* Patience needed for completion

